review_blob: Enjoyed this beer. Perfect amount of tartness. Great flavor with a little too much bready yeast aftertaste to make it perfect. The only downfall is the aroma which has banana/yeast bready aroma. Overall very enjoyable
Had at a tasting. Fantastic sour and like nothing I have ever had. It was like a smoky sour.
Had at a tasting. Very good and need to seek out again. Will update the review after i have again.
Awesome Sour. Had at a tasting. One of the best I have had. Will elaborate on the review after i buy another.
Drank in snifter. Bottled on 12/12. Definitely one of the best if not the best beer I have ever had. Super smooth and drinkable with just the right amount of hops. Loved it!

Drank from tulip glass poured from bomber from alaska. Aroma - caramel hoppy aroma. Appearance - beautiful golden orange coloe with medium head. Taste - dense piny, hoppy with caramal malt hints. Delicious! Palate - lot of pine and some alcohol. Very bitter aftertaste Overall - delicious IIPA. Very enjoyable.

Drank in snifter poured from bomber. Aroma - very nice with a hint of orange citrus smell. Appearance - some trub in a beautiful golden hue. Moderate froth. Taste - smooth but a little bitter. You can taste the orange zest/pulp. Palate - bitter and zesty. Literally. Overall - very nice but maybe a bit too bitter from the pulp.

Drank from bomber poured into tulip. Aroma - caramelized. Not all that happy or floral. Appearance - dark auburn. Frothy head. Taste - smooth but taste of amber is heavy. Palate - some bitterness. Almost like a weathers candy. Overall - not bad but not great. Decent IP but too much amber flavor.

Drank from tulip poured from bomber from Alaska. Aroma - copper aroma. Nothing enticing. Appearance - dark ruby auburn with light froth. Taste - not bad. I dont like red/amber beers but enough hops and malt to balance it out. Palate - same as taste. Hoppy burnt mouth feel. Overall - not bad. Very drinkable for the style.
Not a huge fan of this one. Tastes more like a happy amber than anything else. Dark auburn color and an apple aroma. Will not drink again

Drank in tulip glass poured from bomber from alaska. Aroma - not much of an aroma clean scent. Not heavy on hop aroma. Appearance - beautiful glowing orangish red. Burnt rubber color. Taste - boom. Fantastic. So smooth and tasty with just enough bitterness. Loving it. Palate - nice bitter finish. Overall - very very enjoyable. One of my favorite DIPAs.

Drank from bottle poured into tulip. Got from Alaska bottle shop. Aroma - very piny but fresh aroma. Appearance - cloudy dark orange. Thick froth. Taste - good but very bitter. Palate - think burnt mouth feel and bitterness. Overall - pretty good. Not in love.

Drank in tulip poured from 12oz bottle. Aroma - nice blend of pine and citrus. Appearance - dark auburn/light forth Taste - very refreshing and piny. Smooth. Palate - burnt wood flavor. Overall - very enjoyable off the radar IPA. I really liked it.

Drank in tulip poured from bomber. Aroma - dry woody aroma. Lacking hop scents. Appearance - murky golden orange. Light froth. Taste - peppery and smooth but not as bitter or floral as I like. Palate - little more bitter. Overall - good but not great.

Drank from bomber poured in tulip glass. Aroma - perfect blend of citrus and hops. Appearance - golden orange/auburn with medium froth and heavy lacing. Taste - fired wood taste. Bitter but not overly bitter. Enjoyable. Could use a little more citrus for my liking. Palate - same as taste - bitter but still pleasant. Overall - very very good. Almost one of the best double IPAs but a little bitter still.

Drank in tulip glass poured from bomber. Aroma - light citrus notes. Nothing overwhelming. Appearamce - golden auburn. Little darker than most ipas. Taste - very fresh with just the right amount of bittering hops. Very drinkable. Palate - good with a bit more bitter to it. Overall - good IPA. Very smooth but not out of the ordinary

Aroma - vanilla bourbon smell. Light coffee notes. Appearance - dark auburn brown. Almost black. Taste - bourbon like ale. Little strong. Palate - whooo. Very strong and hot. Overall - not my type of beer. I like bourbon barrel aged stouts but the pale al is just too much for.

Drank in tulip from 22oz bottle. Aroma - sour and vinegar smell. Very nice. Appearance - beautiful golden blush color. Taste - sour but a little skunk at end. Good though. Palate - super sour and I like it. Overall - pretty good sour. Not my favorite but good

Drank in oversized wine glass from bomber. Aroma - smells like Brett/sour beer. Very nice. Appearance. Cloudy yellow with no head. Taste - sweet on tongue. Good sour flavor with a little heat from the Chiles in my throat. Palate - more Chile and sour. Overall - very very enjoyable. Sour and smooth

Drank in tulip from 22oz bottle. Aroma - licorice and molasses aroma. Appearance - dark black and thin. Light froth. Taste - smooth like a light stout or porter. Palate - sweet mouthfeel. Overall - good black ipa. Very drinkable
beer_name: Midnight Sun XXX Black Double IPA

review_blob: Drank from tulip poured from bomber. Aroma - very nice citrus aroma from hops. Appearance - beautiful golden orange with nice carbonation and froth. Taste - very nice. Buttery and caramel with citrus hops. Palate - some sulfure/burnt mouthfeel. Not my ideal. Overall - good ipa. Still not my favorite besides the hype but tasty overall

Drank from snifter poured from bomber. Aroma - very clean citrusy hops. Appearance - murky golden orange with frothy head. Taste - grapefruit and rye flavors   very smooth. Palate - almost a sweet rye hoppiness. Fantastic! Overall- really nice ipa. Smooth and tasty
beer_name: Hoppin Frog Hopped-Up Goose Juice Rye IPA

review_blob: Drank in tulip glass poured from bomber. Aroma - belgian yeasty aroma. Typical beligian style beer. Appearance - golden yellow with very frothy head. Taste - sweet first taste with beligian blonde aftertaste. Bready with some spice. Palate  - explodes with froth in mouth. Nice flavor though. Overall - better than most belgian style beers but still not my favorite.
UPDATED: MAY 14, 2013

Poured from 12 oz bottle into tulip glass, aroma - very nice blend of citrus and hops. Grapefruit. Appearance - beautiful golden orange color. Taste - good citrys flavor but too much malt for me. Not bad. Palate - same as taste. Get a strong boozy malty mouthfeel. Overall - ok. Not my favoirite dipa
beer_name: Terrapin Side Project Hopzilla Double IPA

review_blob: Drank in tulip glass poured from 12oz bottle. Aroma - tart aroma with light blackberry notes. Appearance - amber colored with light froth. Taste - strong sour notes with a little bit of red wine taste. Palate - very sour and funky mouthfeel. Overall - really good sour but not my favorite

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: Drank in tulip poured frombomber.  Aroma - very stong citrus/lemon. Not much hops. Appearance - light golden yellow. Lighter than most ipas. Taste - citrusy and pale. Lacking hops. Not very bitter. Palate - very sweet palate. Overall - pretty good but a bit sweet.

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: Drank in tulip poured from 12.7oz bottle. Aroma- great bourbon smells like barrel aged. Appearance - silky black with no lacing. Taste - sweet but strong bourbon flavors. Very drinkable but strong and alcohol heat. Palate - alchohol and licorice. Overall- very pleased. Havent heard it was a BA but tastes likke one. Very very good.

Drank from 12oz can poured into tulip glass. Aroma - fresh and citurs hops. Very clean. Appearance - pretty golden orange with thick but small froth. Taste - good blend of hops and citrus. Very drinkable. Palate - wet hop palate. Good flavor. Overall - very nice ipa. Doesnt stand out as my favorite but nothing wrong at all. Good stuff
beer_name: Cigar City Jai Alai India Pale Ale

review_blob: Drank in snifter poured from 12oz bottle. Aroma - roasted coffee/chocolate malt. Appearance - very dark brown with light colored  frothy head. Taste - whooo. Very potent with alcohol and sweet coffee. Very good and im bout to be drunk. Palate - heavy booze and heat. Nice chocolate taste. Overall - very hot but still great to sip on. Very enjoyable.

Drank in pint poured from 12 oz bottle. Aroma - roasted chocolate and coffee nots. Appearance - pours and looks like a stout with little froth. Taste - fantastic porter. Rich and roasted. Get the coffee bean flavor. Palate - a little more heat on the mouth feel but still fantastic. Overall best porter I have had. Very very good.

Drank from pilsner glass poured from can. Aroma - dead on with wheat and pineapple aroma. Appearance - murky golden orange with thick froth. Taste - sweet pineapple and wheat flavors. Fairly smooth. Palate - very bitter/sweet mouthfeel. Overall - pretty good. Probably will not buy again

Drank in tulip glass poured from 12oz bottle. Aroma - not much of anything for an ipa. Dry notes of wood. Apppearance - golden orange with some sediment floating around. Taste - not as hoppy or piny as most ipas. Bitter but still smooth. Palate - little bit more piny now. Overall- pretty good. Not my favorite but not too bad. Wouldnt seek out again but would drink

Drank in pilsner glass poured from 12oz bottle. Aroma - not much going on here. Appearance - translucent yellow. Could pass as a bud light. Taste - avg pilsner taste. Light with lacking body. Palate- ugh. Like burnt pee if I ever had it. Overall - not my style of beer but drinkable like a Bud light

Poured in IPA glass from 22oz bottle. Aroma - piny aromas nothing spectacular. Appearance - auburn golden color with medium forth and carbonation. Taste - some hops but more amber than anything. Not bad. Palate - same as taste. Nothing spectacular. Overall - decent beer. Will not seek out again.

Drank in snifter poured from bomber. Aroma - citrus aroma with nice hop notes. Appearance  beautiful golden orange with small but for thy head. Looks very nice!! Taste - tastes like BBQ oranges with some hops. Very nice and drinkable. Palate - different than most IPAs. Not a dry happy finish but wetter. Overall - very good beer but doesnt fall into my top ten ipas

Drank in tall pilsner glass poured from 220z bottle. Aroma - roasted earthy smell. Appearance - golden auburn with avg froth and carbonation. Taste - caramel and hazelnut. Palate - get some burnt caramel taste. Overall - tastes like an upgrade to a red or amber beer. A little more flavor but still not my favorite. Really good for the style though

beer_brewer_name: Brasserie des Sources (formerly: de St. Amand)
review_blob: Poured in pilsner glass from bomber. Aroma - not bad. Typical aroma of a belgian banana/soap. Appearance - light amber. Taste- avg mix between a pale ale and a belgian. Palate - not great. Overall - i know this is a poor review but I think it has aged too long. I had one before that I enjoyed.

Drank from 22oz bottle poured into tulip glass. Aroma - wonderful blend of citrus and hops. Appearance - golden orange with light carbonation and froth. Taste - bold grapefruit and hops taste. Very enjoyable! Palate - more dry hops on palate. Overall - very nice IPA.

Poured from bomber into tulip glass. Aroma - yeast/malt with citrus and spice. Appearance - cloudy golden yellow with thick froth. Taste - avvg Belgian beer taste. Cloves and bananas notes. Lemon zest with a bit of soap. Palate - same as taste but get some heat. Overall - not my favorite type of style so I may be biased. Not good in my book but had to drink for the occasion.
beer_name: Ommegang Game of Thrones #1 - Iron Throne Ale

review_blob: Drank in tulip glass. Aroma - a musty sour smell. Rasberry but rotten. Appearance - dark cherry color. No head. No carbonation. Taste - taste gets better. Tastes like an oaked sour. Sweet and bitter. Palate - not bad. Gets stronger with mouthfeel. Overall - good taste but on this rating system thats all it gets. Good thing it is the most important. Not bad overall. Will not seek it out again

Drank in snifter poured from 22oz bottle. Aroma - nice but subtle notes of coffee and cocoa. Appearance- thinner than typical stout. Auburnish black color with light froth. Taste - very nice. Clean cocoa/coffee taste. Not overwhelming. Drinkable. Palate - lacking something here. More malty than anything. Overall- pretty good cap stout. Not my favorite but the bottle will get drunk
UPDATED: MAR 28, 2013
UPDATED: APR 25, 2013

Drank from bomber poured into tulip glass. Aroma- nice citrus notes but nothing overwhelming. Appearance- beautiful golden orange with very nice glow. Taste - not as hoppy as i would expect from a DIPA but is great for the summer season. Very smooth with a bit of butter. Palate- piny and citrus palate. Very nice. Overall- this is a good everyday beer but nothing that makes it stand out

Drank from bomber poured into pilsner glass. Aroma- nice hoppy aroma. Appearance- auburn red with frothy head. Taste- color is decieving. Tastes like a sweet ipa. The hops show through. Palate- very nice dry hoppy mouthfeel. Overall- impressed as I typically do not like red or amber beers.

Drank in snifter glass poured from bomber. Aroma- solid saison smell with a bit of lemon. Appearance- pale in color. Similiar to a blah pilsner. Taste- exactly what i expected. Half pinot grigio and half typical saison with some champagne kick. Very drinkable. Palate- a little more alcohol and lemon. Very good.  Overall- very good. A little different. Outside the siason box but really good.

Drank in tulip beer glass poured from 12 oz bottle. Aroma- lots of citrus with notes of hop. Appearance- golden orange grapefruit color. Light head and carbonation. Taste- has a major lemon kick. More than other ipas. Very drinkable and tasty. Palate- hop explosion with a citrus kick. Very nice. Overall- another great IPA. Im on a streak. Very enjoyable.

Drank in snifter from 22oz bomber. Aroma- mostly barley and oatmeal flavor. Nothing stands out. Appearance- dark black. Pours like oil with no head. Taste- great pepperylike black coffee with a kick. Palate- oh yeah! Best part. Like good coffee in your mouth. Overall- fantastic. One of my favorite stouts. Very clean without too much going on.

Drank in pilsner poured from 12 oz bottle. Smells more like rye beer than the red rey from founders. Can smell the alcohol. Appearance- dark auburn color with no carbonation or head. Taste - lots of yeast and malt flavors. Almost like beer drenched bread. Its ok. Not my favorite beer. Somewhat like an amber ale. Palate- poor mouthfeel. Get the heat and barf flavor. Not a fan. Overall- its ok. Will not drink again but still better than expected from a scotch drink.
